WARNING: This is an alpha version (i.e.  working but unstable)!
See README for requirements to build.

1. Get the latest version from github:
git clone https://github.com/lorenzosu/jackmatrix.git
cd jackmatrix/
git checkout revision

2. Create configure script and other files for the autotools (not included)
autoreconf --install

3. Configure and make
./configure
make

4. If everything was ok, to run do:
cd src/
./jackmatrix 

5. To install:
make install (usually as root, in the jackmatrix dir)

6. To uninstall:
make uninstall (as root if you did the previous comand as root)